.TH QHW_ADM_POLICY 3 "2026-07-05" "qhw-admission" "qhw-admission manual"
.SH NAME
qhw_adm_load_policy, qhw_adm_add_policy_path,
qhw_adm_set_policy \- load and select admission policies
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include <qhw_admission/qhw_admission.h>

qhw_adm_rc_t qhw_adm_load_policy(
	qhw_adm_t *ctx,
	const char *path,
	qhw_adm_policy_t **out_policy);

qhw_adm_rc_t qhw_adm_add_policy_path(
	qhw_adm_t *ctx,
	const char *path);

qhw_adm_rc_t qhw_adm_set_policy(
	qhw_adm_t *ctx,
	uint64_t device_id,
	const char *name,
	const qhw_adm_kv_t *options,
	size_t option_count);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Policies are shared-object plugins. Loading a policy validates its exported
.B qhw_adm_policy_plugin
symbol and registers its name with the context.
.PP
.BR qhw_adm_add_policy_path ()
adds a directory searched by
.BR qhw_adm_set_policy ().
.PP
.BR qhw_adm_set_policy ()
selects one policy for a registered device and initializes policy-private
state with the supplied options.
.SH STANDARD POLICIES
.TP
.B unlimited
Accepts valid requests when the device is available.
.TP
.B credit
Reserves finite baseline-unit credits.
.TP
.B rate
Reserves finite throughput slices.
.SH RETURN VALUES
Policy functions return
.B QHW_ADM_OK
on success. Common failures include
.B QHW_ADM_ERR_NOT_FOUND,
.B QHW_ADM_ERR_EXISTS,
.B QHW_ADM_ERR_POLICY,
.B QHW_ADM_ERR_UNSUPPORTED,
and
.B QHW_ADM_ERR_STATE.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR qhw_admission (3),
.BR qhw_adm_reservation (3),
.BR qhw_adm_types (3)
